<segment id="1" parent="1001" relname="preparation">2. Ballastless Track Structure</segment>
<segment id="2" parent="1002" relname="preparation">Multilayer Synthetic Aperture Focusing Technique</segment>
<segment id="3" parent="1004" relname="preparation">Method</segment>
<segment id="4" parent="1005" relname="preparation">2.1. SAFT Imaging Method</segment>
<segment id="5" parent="1005" relname="sequence">The principle of the SAFT imaging method is shown in</segment>
<segment id="6" parent="7" relname="preparation">Figure 1</segment>
<segment id="7" parent="1007" relname="span">.</segment>
<segment id="8" parent="1005" relname="sequence">In a group of ultrasonic transducer arrays , ultrasonic waves are sequentially emitted by one probe .</segment>
<segment id="9" parent="1010" relname="span">The other probes receive ultrasonic waves .</segment>
<segment id="10" parent="9" relname="elaboration">The received ultrasonic echo signals are processed by DAS .</segment>
<segment id="11" parent="1005" relname="sequence">Lastly , a reconstructed B-scan image is produced .</segment>
<segment id="12" parent="1015" relname="span">When information such as the position and size of the defects in the object</segment>
<segment id="13" parent="12" relname="elaboration">to be measured</segment>
<segment id="14" parent="1014" relname="same_unit">are unknown ,</segment>
<segment id="15" parent="1016" relname="span">SAFT imaging can be used</segment>
<segment id="16" parent="1017" relname="span">to calculate the value of all the pixels</segment>
<segment id="17" parent="16" relname="means">by traversing the imaging region .</segment>
<segment id="18" parent="1005" relname="sequence">As shown in</segment>
<segment id="19" parent="1020" relname="preparation">Figure 1</segment>
<segment id="20" parent="1022" relname="attribution">, it is assumed</segment>
<segment id="21" parent="1023" relname="span">that the sensor position is un</segment>
<segment id="22" parent="21" relname="elaboration">( n = 1 , 2 , 3 ... n ) ,</segment>
<segment id="23" parent="1022" relname="contrast">while the exciting sensor position coordinates are ( xi , zi ) .</segment>
<segment id="24" parent="1020" relname="sequence">The receiving sensor position coordinates are ( xj , zj ) .</segment>
<segment id="25" parent="1020" relname="sequence">The position coordinate of any pixel D is ( x , z ) .</segment>
