<segment id="29" parent="1030" relname="span">and then reaches the position of the receiving sensor uj via point D ,</segment>
<segment id="30" parent="1032" relname="span">as shown in Equation ( 1 ) :</segment>
<segment id="31" parent="30" relname="evidence">( 1 )</segment>
<segment id="32" parent="1033" relname="joint">where the ri is given by :</segment>
<segment id="33" parent="1035" relname="span">and v is the speed</segment>
<segment id="34" parent="1036" relname="span">at which sound waves travel in the object</segment>
<segment id="35" parent="34" relname="elaboration">being measured ,</segment>
<segment id="36" parent="1035" relname="elaboration">i , j = 1,2,3 … n .</segment>
<segment id="37" parent="1039" relname="circumstance">When the exciting and receiving transducer positions are ui and uj , respectively ,</segment>
<segment id="38" parent="1042" relname="span">the value of any pixel D</segment>
<segment id="39" parent="38" relname="restatement">( x , z )</segment>
